# Color System - CRITICAL RULES

## Exact Brand Colors

ALWAYS use these Tailwind classes. NEVER use arbitrary values like `bg-[#E87722]`.

### Primary Palette
- `bg-forest-green` / `text-forest-green` - #004928
  - Navigation bars, section headers, primary text areas
  
- `bg-burnt-orange` / `text-burnt-orange` - #E87722
  - **PRIMARY CTA COLOR - Use for ALL main call-to-action buttons**
  
- `bg-amber` / `text-amber` - #F5A623
  - Secondary CTAs, highlights, hover states on secondary buttons

- `bg-mint` / `text-mint` - #10E397
  - Minor accents only, hover states on links, decorative elements

### Neutrals
- `bg-charcoal` / `text-charcoal` - #26251E (body text)
- `bg-warm-light` - #F2F1EC (page backgrounds)
- `bg-light` - #F7F7F4 (card backgrounds)

## Button Color Hierarchy

### ✅ CORRECT Usage
```html
<!-- Primary action - burnt orange -->
<button class="btn-primary">Book møde</button>

<!-- Secondary action - amber -->
<button class="btn-secondary">Læs mere</button>

<!-- Link with mint accent -->
<a href="#" class="link-mint">Se alle stillinger →</a>
```

### ❌ WRONG Usage
```html
<!-- NEVER use mint for primary CTAs -->
<button class="bg-mint">Book møde</button>

<!-- NEVER use arbitrary color values -->
<button class="bg-[#E87722]">Click me</button>

<!-- NEVER use inline styles -->
<button style="background-color: #E87722">Click me</button>
```

## Color Decision Tree

1. **Is it a PRIMARY call-to-action?** → Use `burnt-orange`
2. **Is it a SECONDARY action?** → Use `amber`
3. **Is it a text link or small accent?** → Use `mint`
4. **Is it navigation or headers?** → Use `forest-green`
5. **Is it body text?** → Use `charcoal`
6. **Is it a page background?** → Use `warm-light`
7. **Is it a card background?** → Use `light`

## Forbidden Practices
- ❌ No hex codes in HTML/templates
- ❌ No RGB/HSL values
- ❌ No inline styles
- ❌ No custom color names
- ❌ No arbitrary Tailwind values: `bg-[#abc123]`
